<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12218b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12218b">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12218b"> 218(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">C</font> = SP&apos;s &lsquo;faute&rsquo;</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">La <cite>Confession</cite> parle, il est vrai, des conversions op&eacute;r&eacute;es par Patrick, de ses tribulations, de son asc&eacute;tisme. Mais c&apos;est qu&apos;elle a pour but <mark>de d&eacute;fendre son auteur contre une accusation d&apos;indignit&eacute; qui avait &eacute;t&eacute; port&eacute;e contre lui</mark>. On venait de proclamer qu&apos;il avait jadis commis un p&eacute;ch&eacute; qui entra&icirc;nait sa d&eacute;ch&eacute;ance de la dignit&eacute; &eacute;piscopale. Or <mark>Patrick ne nie pas sa faute, quoiqu&apos;il se plaigne de ce que ce soit un ancien ami qui soit son accusateur</mark> <br><font color="green">[The <cite>Confession</cite> speaks, it is true, of Patrick&apos;s conversions, his tribulations and his asceticism. But its real aim is to defend the author against an accusation of infamy that has been raised against him. There was an announcement that he had committed a sin which resulted in the forfeiture of his episcopal dignity. But Patrick does not deny his fault, although he complains that it was an old friend who accused him.]</font> <small> Stefan Czarnowski, <a name="SCSP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SCSP"><cite title="source">Le culte des h&eacute;ros et ses conditions sociale: saint Patrick, h&eacute;ros nationale de l'Irlande</cite></a> (1919) 35</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
